projectDescription: | 
    <em>project: kilter</em> is a design project for UMD's INST451 class. The professor requested the class to design for a
    personal passion; my focus was weightlifting. Also, teaching staff provided mentorship during our five
    design sprints in the semester. The objective of the class was UI/UX and not the programming of the interfaces.
    <br>
    <br>
    Weightlifters with 2+ years experience lack tools truly optimized for their workflow. Spreadsheets and plain-text 
    methods are functional and customizable, but weren't designed with weightlifters in mind.
    <em>project: kilter</em> seeks to optimize current methods of tracking personal fitness by offering a user-friendly 
    interface, modular features, and leveraging the community through the plugins system.

